gene_chromosome_ensembl.label: Chromosome
gene_chromosome_ensembl.description: Chromosome where a gene is located

gene_number_of_paralogs_homologene.label: # of paralogs
gene_number_of_paralogs_homologene.description: Number of duplicated genes (paralogs) in each human gene calculated based on HomoloGene

gene_evolutionary_conservation_homologen.label: Evolutionary divergence
gene_evolutionary_conservation_homologen.description: Most distant organisms from human that have orthologous genes in HomoloGene

gene_high_level_expression_refex.label: Tissue-specific high expression (RefEx GeneChip)
gene_high_level_expression_refex.description: Tissues in which a gene was tissue-specific highly expressed in 34 tissues of RefEx(GeneChip microarray)

source.label: Calculations for tissue specificity of genechip human GSE7307 from RefEx

gene_low_level_expression_refex.label: Tissue-specific low expression (RefEx GeneChip)
gene_low_level_expression_refex.description: Tissues in which a gene was tissue-specific lowly expressed in 34 tissues of RefEx(GeneChip microarray)

source.label: Calculations for tissue specificity of genechip human GSE7307 from RefEx

gene_high_level_expression_gtex6.label: Tissue-specific high expression (GTEx)
gene_high_level_expression_gtex6.description: Tissues in which a gene is tissue-specific highly expressed in 49 tissues of GTEx V6

gene_not_expressed_in_tissues_gtex.label: No expression in tissues (GTEx)
gene_not_expressed_in_tissues_gtex.description: Tissues in which expression of a gene is not detected in 53 tissues of GTEx V8

gene_specific_expression_in_tissues_hpa.label: Tissue-specific high expression (HPA)
gene_specific_expression_in_tissues_hpa.description: Tissues in which expression specificity of a gene is evaluated as "Tissue enriched", "Tissue enhanced", or"Group enriched" by Human Protein Atlas

source.label: HPA (Data from the Human Protein Atlas in tab-separated format)

gene_specific_expression_in_cells_hpa.label: Cell type-specific high expression (HPA)
gene_specific_expression_in_cells_hpa.description: Cell types in which expression specificity of a gene is evaluated as "Cell type enriched", "Cell type enhanced", or"Group enriched" by Human Protein Atlas

source.label: HPA (Data from the Human Protein Atlas in tab-separated format)

protein_cellular_component_uniprot.label: Cellular component
protein_cellular_component_uniprot.description: Functional annotations (GO terms) derived from the Cellular component category of GeneOntology, which Uniprot has assigned to each human protein with evidence information

source.label: Gene ontology cellular component annotation from UniProt

protein_biological_process_uniprot.label: Biological process
protein_biological_process_uniprot.description: Functional annotations (GO terms) derived from the Biological process category of GeneOntology, which Uniprot has assigned to each human protein with evidence information

source.label: Gene ontology biological process annotation from UniProt

protein_molecular_function_uniprot.label: Molecular function
protein_molecular_function_uniprot.description: Functional annotations (GO terms) derived from the Molecular function category of GeneOntology, which Uniprot has assigned to each human protein with evidence information

source.label: Gene ontology molecular function annotation from UniProt

protein_ligands_uniprot.label: Ligands
protein_ligands_uniprot.description: Classification by non-protein molecules which bind/react with proteins in Function section from UniProt

protein_molecular_mass_uniprot.label: Molecular mass
protein_molecular_mass_uniprot.description: Molecular weight of the protein including information from multiple isoforms in Sequences section from UniProt

protein_ptms_uniprot.label: PTMs
protein_ptms_uniprot.description: Classification by types of post-translational modifications, including S-S bonds (disulfide bonds) in Amino acid modifications section from UniProt

protein_number_of_transmembrane_domains_.label: # of transmembrane domains
protein_number_of_transmembrane_domains_.description: Number of transmembrane domains. A group of molecules forming a family, such as channels, may have the same number of domains in Topology section from UniProt

protein_number_of_phosphorylation_sites_.label: # of phosphorylation sites
protein_number_of_phosphorylation_sites_.description: Number of phosphorylation at Ser/Thr/Tyr, which may create an activation state for the protein and acts like a switch in Amino acid modifications section from UniProt

protein_number_of_glycosylation_sites_un.label: # of glycosylation sites
protein_number_of_glycosylation_sites_un.description: Number of glycosylation sites, including N-linked,O-linked and others in Amino acid modifications section from UniProt

protein_disease_related_proteins_uniprot.label: Disease-related proteins
protein_disease_related_proteins_uniprot.description: Disease-related proteins in Pathology & Biotech section from UniProt

protein_isolation_source_uniprot.label: Tissues w/expression reported
protein_isolation_source_uniprot.description: Classification based on the name of the tissue from which the clone was isolated in the reference describing the protein sequence in Tissue section from UniProt

protein_evidence_of_existence_nextprot.label: Evidence of existence
protein_evidence_of_existence_nextprot.description: Classification by the basis of protein expression, such as whether it has been identified as a protein or transcript in Expression section from neXtProt

structure_data_existence_uniprot.label: Structure data existence
structure_data_existence_uniprot.description: Uniprot entries having 3D structure data in PDB in Structure section from Uniprot

structure_helical_regions_uniprot.label: Rate of helical regions
structure_helical_regions_uniprot.description: Rate of helical regions in each entry of UniProt

structure_beta_strand_regions_uniprot.label: Rate of beta strand regions
structure_beta_strand_regions_uniprot.description: Rate of beta strand regions in each entry of UniProt

structure_number_of_peptides_pdb.label: # of peptides in a PDB entry
structure_number_of_peptides_pdb.description: The number of peptides in a PDB entry

structure_analysis_methods_pdb.label: Analysis methods
structure_analysis_methods_pdb.description: Classification by the method used to determine the three-dimensional structure in Experimental method section from PDB

interaction_proteins_in_pathway_reactome.label: Proteins in pathway
interaction_proteins_in_pathway_reactome.description: Proteins participating as components classified by pathway (reaction) from Reactome

interaction_compounds_in_pathway_reactom.label: Compounds in pathway
interaction_compounds_in_pathway_reactom.description: Compounds participating as components classified by pathway (reaction) from Reactome

interaction_number_of_interacting_protei.label: # of interacting proteins
interaction_number_of_interacting_protei.description: Classification of uniprot proteins by the number of target proteins they interact with in Interaction section from UniProt

interaction_chembl_assay_existence_unipr.label: ChEMBL assay existence
interaction_chembl_assay_existence_unipr.description: Uniprot entries classified according to the presence or absence of a method to detect direct protein-compound interactions (ChEMBL assay)

source.label: Target protein from ChEMBL-RDF 28.0 against all UniProt entries

compound_chemical_role_chebi.label: Chemical role
compound_chemical_role_chebi.description: Classification based on the chemical roles, such as antioxidant or environmental contaminant from ChEBI

compound_application_type_chebi.label: Application type
compound_application_type_chebi.description: Classification based on the application types, such as pharmaceutical or pesticide from ChEBI

compound_action_type_chembl.label: Action type
compound_action_type_chembl.description: Classification based on the mechanism of action, such as an inhibitor or an antagonist from ChEMBL

compound_biological_role_chebi.label: Biological role
compound_biological_role_chebi.description: Classification based on the biological roles, such as inhibitor or antimicrobial agent from ChEBI

compound_drug_indication_mesh_chembl.label: Drug indication
compound_drug_indication_mesh_chembl.description: Classification of diseases for which drugs are indicated, based on hierarchical data using MeSH, a life science thesaurus from ChEMBL

compound_drug_development_phase_chembl.label: Drug development phase
compound_drug_development_phase_chembl.description: Classification based on the drug's development phase (research stage, phase I-III, and post-launch) from ChEMBL

compound_atc_classification_pubchem.label: PubChem ATC classification
compound_atc_classification_pubchem.description: Classification of a medicine (in PubChem) according to its medicinal properties (WHO ATC Code)

compound_atc_classification_chembl.label: ChEMBL ATC classification
compound_atc_classification_chembl.description: Classification of a medicine (in ChEMBL) according to its medicinal properties (WHO ATC Code)

glycan_mass_glycosmos.label: Molecular mass of glycans
glycan_mass_glycosmos.description: Molecular weight of glycans from GlyCosmos

glycan_subsumption_glycosmos.label: Subsumption
glycan_subsumption_glycosmos.description: The relationship between four levels of glycan types registered in GlyCosmos. For details, see the Help page of GlyCosmos.

disease_diseases_mondo.label: Diseases in Mondo
disease_diseases_mondo.description: Subcategories in the Disease or disorder category in the Mondo Disease Ontology (Mondo)

disease_diseases_mesh.label: Diseases in MeSH
disease_diseases_mesh.description: Subcategories in the Disease category in Medical Subject Headings (MeSH)

disease_diseases_nando.label: Diseases in NANDO
disease_diseases_nando.description: Japanese rare and intractable disease categories in the Nanbyo Disease Ontology (NANDO)

disease_related_dbs_mondo.label: Cross referenced disease DBs in Mondo
disease_related_dbs_mondo.description: Number of entries linked to Mondo in each of approx. 70 disease related databases from database cross reference in Mondo

disease_phenotypic_abnormality_hpo.label: Phenotypic abnormality
disease_phenotypic_abnormality_hpo.description: Classification the subcategories of the Phenotypic abnormality categories of the Human Phenotype Ontology (HPO)

variant_gwas_togovar.label: GWAS
variant_gwas_togovar.description: Classification of statistically significant variants in genome-wide association studies (GWAS) based on associated traits. Obtained from GWAS catalog via TogoVar

variant_clinical_significance_togovar.label: Clinical significance
variant_clinical_significance_togovar.description: Classification of variants according to their clinical significance, such as whether they are the cause of the disease or not. Obtained from ClinVar via TogoVar
